<item>
            <title>[HBASE-16990] Shell tool to dump table schemas and table privileges</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16990</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Recently,  we are trying to migrate tables from Cluster-A to Cluster-B,  I found that HBase lack some useful tools :&lt;br/&gt;
1.  dump table schema,  like mysqldump in mysql&lt;br/&gt;
2.  dump table privileges,  like pt-show-grants in mysql provided by Percona. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we can add a dump sub-command looks like (JUST simple demo) : &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
$ ./bin/hbase dump  -t test_table  --with-privileges  &amp;gt; ~/test_table.hsh

$ cat ~/test_table.hsh
create &apos;test_table&apos;, {NAME=&amp;gt;&apos;f1&apos;} 
grant &apos;test_user&apos;, &apos;RW&apos;, &apos;test_table&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe I can contribute ...  &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How do you think ?  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
